acceptance_criteria: "(1) Forward backlog of open, well-defined items covers genuine future work + coverage gaps surfaced by per-domain audits; (2) Architectural ADRs recorded for real undocumented decisions; (3) Roadmap milestone + capability epics anchor the backlog; (4) Agent/user stories captured; (5) No duplicate items (every create dedup-checked via pm search); (6) Existing closed items are NOT modified (would mis-attribute them to this release in the changelog); (7) pm health/validate stay ok; (8) CI green + AI-bot review clean; (9) Sentry + telemetry verified post-change."
definition_of_ready: Per-domain read-only audits completed by specialized sub-agents; their work-logs and decisions recorded in pm under per-domain tracking tasks.
goal: project management = context management
objective: "Make the tracker a complete, organized, living representation of the ecosystem (not just a completed-work log)"
value: "Future work, decisions, stories, and goals become discoverable context for humans and agents via pm"
impact: Agents get optimal next-work context; contributors see the roadmap and the why behind the architecture
outcome: "An organized forward backlog (open), architectural ADRs (recorded), a roadmap milestone, and agent/user stories — all dedup-checked"
why_now: "Tracker has 902 items but ZERO open/in-progress: rich history, no living map. pm context returns empty. Best-practice PM needs a forward layer."
